SUMMARY:BIG In-Person/Online Meetup (East Columbia Branch Library)
DESCRIPTION:In-person is at the East Columbia Branch Library in the Marvin Thomas Room. \nJoin us IN-PERSON or ONLINE. Anyone with an interest in game design and development is welcome\, from beginners to veteran professionals. \nWe will be meeting in the Marvin Thomas Room at the East Columbia Branch Library (6600 Cradlerock Way). (Not an official Howard County Library System event.) \nIf you want to attend virtually\, the Discord server link is provided in the main monthly (1st of the month) meetup details. An organizer will ensure that a laptop is provided on-site to connect the Discord attendees with those physically on-site. It takes us a few minutes to set up the projector\, so hold tight when you join the Discord voice chat channel. We’ll be there soon!
URL:https://baltimoreindiegames.com/event/big-in-person-online-meetup-east-columbia-branch-library-3/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260606T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260606T170000
DTSTAMP:20260505T001559
CREATED:20251216T003403Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251216T003403Z
UID:387-1780743600-1780765200@baltimoreindiegames.com
SUMMARY:Indie Game Fest
DESCRIPTION:The Enoch Pratt Free Library hosts the annual Indie Video Game Fest\, a curated\, curious\, and creative exhibition of Independent Video Games from the DMV area. \nIndie Video Game Fest is an annual one-day event that brings together gamers\, developers\, and video game industry insiders to play\, discuss\, and celebrate independent video games from across the DMV area. \nAs part of the event\, we host exciting guest speakers from the video game industry. These talks focus on the creation of video games\, the video game industry\, and what working in it is like. Previous speakers include Jason Schreier\, Chris Bratt\, and Jake Solomon. \nIf you’re an indie game developer who’s interested in showing your game\, complete the submission form at the link below before February 28\, 2026\, at 5 pm: \nhttps://www.prattlibrary.org/indie-game-fest \n 
URL:https://baltimoreindiegames.com/event/indie-game-fest-2/
LOCATION:Enoch Pratt Free Library\, 400 Cathedral Street\, Baltimore\, MD\, 21201\, United States
END:VEVENT
